sql:
SELECT pws_name
FROM water_systems
WHERE population_served > 10000;

SELECT AVG(num_site_visits) AS avg_site_visits
FROM water_systems
WHERE status = 'active';

SELECT pws_name
FROM water_systems
ORDER BY num_violations DESC, compliance_score ASC;

SELECT pws_name
FROM water_systems
WHERE compliance_score > 90;

external_knowledge:
- The compliance score is an indicator of how well a public water system meets the regulatory requirements. A higher score implies better compliance; 
- The ranking is based solely on the compliance score, with higher scores indicating better performance; 
- The assumption is that the "top three" systems refer to the best performers in terms of compliance within each county.

sql:
SELECT pws_name, compliance_score
FROM water_systems
ORDER BY compliance_score DESC, pws_name;
